text: Hello (once again not notified about a message, it does need sorting) Thank you for your reply! The story has evolved slightly since I posted but the main plot is still relevant. I am getting closer with my final designs, (as mentioned I only get a few hours a week to make progress on this, slow and steady though) I will send you what I get done today, I have my storyboards up on the wall that are going to be tweaked today as well as my character model sheets finalised.

I love Joanna Quinns work, my lecturer used to work for her so we have had a lot of insight to her work, I would love to achieve something of that standard but preferably through a digital medium as I may not be able to get traditional animation cleaned up in time for my deadline (January for the production and September 2020 for my overall hand-in) :slightly_smiling_face:
I would like to get a feasibility test done for traditional 2D. I would prefer it, but I feel it will be very time consuming, unfortunately.
